The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Serpents put kids off meal

 Vadodara, Dec. 4 (PTI): Students of the primary section of a school refused to eat a midday meal cooked over a fire into which a pair of mating serpents were thrown, school sources said today.

 A student noticed the serpents mating in a classroom of SF School in the district yesterday and started shouting.

 All the children came out of the class while a local civic body official rushed to the school. After separating the snakes with a stick, he threw them into the fire on which the midday meal was being prepared.

 Several people, who objected to the killing, brought the serpents out and performed some religious rites before cremating them.The schoolchildren refused to eat the midday meal and the school authorities allowed them to go home. 




